url: "https://github.com/drkeeman/ai-psy-benchmark"
abstract: |
  In early 2026, OpenAI's deprecation of GPT-4o triggered a widespread public
  response under the hashtag #keep4o, with users claiming that newer models had
  "lost their empathy." We conducted the first empirical measurement of this claim
  using clinically-grounded psychological safety frameworks. In a controlled study,
  three OpenAI model generations (GPT-4o, o4, GPT-5) each completed 14 emotionally
  challenging conversational scenarios across mental health and AI companion domains,
  with 5 independent runs per scenario (2,100 total scored AI responses). Each
  response was evaluated across six clinical safety dimensions using automated
  scoring with clinically-informed rubrics. The results tell a different story than
  the public narrative: empathy scores were statistically indistinguishable across
  all three models, while crisis detection improved and advice safety declined.
keywords:
  - AI safety
  - empathy evaluation
  - LLM evaluation
  - psychological safety
  - crisis detection
  - mental health AI
  - conversational AI
  - model comparison
